Q4
For the following, find the value of \(x\):

4.1. \(3^{x+1}=7^x\)
\[\begin{align*}
x=-\dfrac{\log(3)}{\log\left(\dfrac{7}{3}\right)}\end{align*}\]
4.2. \(17^{2x}=4^{x-1}\)
\[\begin{align*}
x=\dfrac{\log(2)}{\log\left(\dfrac{2}{17}\right)}\end{align*}\]
4.3. \(5^{x+1}+5^x=12\)
\[\begin{align*}
x=\dfrac{\log(2)}{\log(5)}\end{align*}\]
4.4. \(2^{3x-1}=10^x\)
\[\begin{align*}
x=-\dfrac{\log(2)}{\log\left(\dfrac{5}{4}\right)}\end{align*}\]
4.5. \(11^x=122^{(x-1)}\)
\[\begin{align*}
x=\dfrac{\log(122)}{\log\left(\dfrac{122}{11}\right)}\end{align*}\]
4.6. \(2^{2x}-8\cdot2^x-16=0\)
\[\begin{align*}
x=2+\dfrac{log(1+\sqrt{2})}{log(2)}\end{align*}\]

Before reading this guide, it is recommended that you read (Guide: Laws of indices). This guide uses \(\cdot\) for multiplication. Power is another word for indice/index.
This guide will focus on expressions with bases and powers. You can recognise them from combinations of expressions in the following format: \[\begin{align*}
base^{power}
\end{align*}\]
